    <item>
      <title>Elantris</title>
      <link>/2019/02/elantris/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 14 Feb 2019 00:09:10 -0800</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/2019/02/elantris/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;p&gt;Elantris was pretty freaking legit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;thoughts-dump&#34;&gt;Thoughts dump&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s clear that this is an early book, and Sanderson recycles themes.&lt;sup class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; id=&#34;fnref:&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; The main characters here have clear echos with Mistborn &amp;ndash; it&amp;rsquo;s as if Mistborn is an expanded version of Elantris. Arguably not as successful &lt;em&gt;because&lt;/em&gt; it&amp;rsquo;s not as concise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sanderson books feature strong female characters. &lt;sup class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; id=&#34;fnref:tm&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:tm&#34;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;thoughts-dump-2&#34;&gt;Thoughts dump 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;footnotes&#34;&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li id=&#34;fn:&#34;&gt;I never quite understood why recycling themes is such a sin among writers, e.g. criticism of Brian Jacques. The similarity is comforting; the theme is what makes them so enthralling in the first place. But maybe I&amp;rsquo;m just too sentimental.
 &lt;a class=&#34;footnote-return&#34; href=&#34;#fnref:&#34;&gt;&lt;sup&gt;[return]&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li id=&#34;fn:tm&#34;&gt;A sticking point for me.
 &lt;a class=&#34;footnote-return&#34; href=&#34;#fnref:tm&#34;&gt;&lt;sup&gt;[return]&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
